Meals will continue to be served for children 18 years of age and younger. Meal pickups will continue as scheduled each Wednesday.

Heard, Kenilworth & Shaw Montessori Schools will be added to the schedule beginning August 12th. Pick-ups will be communicated the week prior.

Once children return to their classrooms, the health and safety protocols as established and described in the health and safety section will be followed for meals.
.........................

La recogida de comidas seguirán siendo servidas para niños de 18 años o menos cada miércoles.

Escuelas Heard, Kenilworth & Shaw Montessori se agregarán al horario despues del 12 de agosto. Las recogidas se comunicarán la semana anterior.

Una vez que los niños regresan a clases, los protocolos de salud establecidos en la sección de salud y seguridad se seguirán para las comidas.

post_text:
Meet Dr. Elora Diaz, the new President of our Governing Board. Congratulations Dr. Diaz!

"As a first generation college graduate, and a daughter of teenage parents, I know education can transform an individual’s life trajectory. This is why am so grateful for the opportunity to serve my PESD community as the President of the Phoenix Elementary School Board. As President, I am responsible for guiding our Board in establishing the priorities and policies that will support our students in accessing every tool and opportunity they need to succeed. This is not a responsibility I take lightly because we only have one chance to get this right for our kids. To be the best leader I can be for our kids, I will listen. I will listen to our students, to our staff, to our parents, and to our community. I will commit to using my position to elevate the collective priorities of our community and to ensuring equity is not just a term we use, but a value integrated in every aspect of our district." - Dr. Diaz

post_text: Interested in Dual Language Programs? Faith North and Herrera have a perfect partnership.
shared_text:
Herrera School for the Arts and Dual Language
June 10 at 4:22 PM ·

Faith North Early Learning Childhood Center is the perfect partner to Herrera School’s dual language program. Children attending preschool at Faith North are engaged in dual language and are ready to step right into Herrera School’s K-8 model for dual language. The 50/50 model at both schools provides learning in English for half the day and learning in Spanish half the day. The programs emphasize opportunities for authentic engagement as children interact during instruction, playtime and through outdoor experiences.

Let's show some love to our hometown heroes!!
Hometown Heroes is an initiative where Congressional Offices have local elementary schools record 5-10 second videos thanking health care workers and first responders for their bravery and heroism during this unprecedented time in our country.
Record a video or send us a photo thanking your favorite nurse, firefighter, grocery store worker, or anyone who is making a difference during this time. We will compile them and send them to our Congressional Office!

Did you know #dtphx is home to the only chartered 4-H school in Maricopa County? The 4-H program at Lowell School was started by Social Worker Veronica Cons to help students with social and emotional needs, and to develop greater empathy. We are lucky to have held multiple events at Lowell and learned more about the program (and Wilbur 🐷).

Phoenix is home to so many great educators that care deeply about the success of our next generation.

post_text: Consider helping Kenilworth students become future global leaders!
shared_text:
Kenilworth Elementary School
December 3, 2019 at 9:45 AM ·

Our etiquette club needs YOUR help! Consider making a donation to our GoFundMe: http://gf.me/u/wzsysh

The Kenilworth School Etiquette Club is a small group of eighth grade students who are mentored during the academic school year. This mentorship includes, but is not limited to the six pillars of character: trustworthiness, respect, responsibility, fairness, caring and citizenship. The etiquette students will practice the power of presence, body language and communication both verbal and non-verbal. In addition, students will discover proper restaurant etiquette, theatre etiquette and sportsmanship etiquette. Culturally, the etiquette students learn US Continental, European and Asian etiquette. The Kenilworth Etiquette Club is preparing our students to be future leader in the global world in which we live.

post_text: @PhxSchools thanks Fiesta Bowl Charities and Blue Cross Blue Shield of AZ for a record-setting, active day!
shared_text:
Fiesta Bowl
November 13, 2019 at 4:25 PM ·

It was a record-setting day in the Valley of the Sun, as Phoenix Elementary School District #1 students, in conjunction with Fiesta Bowl Charities and Blue Cross Blue Shield of Arizona, set a new Guinness World Records for the largest game of freeze tag this morning!

The event took place with 2,172 students from 13 schools, who came together at Garfield Elementary School in Phoenix to take the title previously set on Sept. 14, 2018, by 1,393 people in Antwerp, Belgium.

“Being out here to set a GUINNESS WORLD RECORD inspires children to believe that they can achieve big accomplishments in life,” said Mike Nealy, #FiestaBowl Executive Director. “Establishing a foundation of health and fitness at an early age is important to the Fiesta Bowl, matching the goals of Blue Cross Blue Shield of Arizona and Phoenix Elementary School District #1.”
